  24:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   *
  25:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   ******************************************************************************
  26:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   @verbatim
  27:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   ==============================================================================
  28:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****                         ##### How to use this driver #####
  29:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   ==============================================================================
  30:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     [..]
  31:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       (#) Initialize the CAN low level resources by implementing the
ARM GAS  C:\WINDOWS\ccJNDTLZ.s 			page 2


  32:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           HAL_CAN_MspInit():
  33:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****          (++) Enable the CAN interface clock using __HAL_RCC_CANx_CLK_ENABLE()
  34:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****          (++) Configure CAN pins
  35:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****              (+++) Enable the clock for the CAN GPIOs
  36:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****              (+++) Configure CAN pins as alternate function
  37:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****          (++) In case of using interrupts (e.g. HAL_CAN_ActivateNotification())
  38:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****              (+++) Configure the CAN interrupt priority using
  39:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****                    HAL_NVIC_SetPriority()
  40:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****              (+++) Enable the CAN IRQ handler using HAL_NVIC_EnableIRQ()
  41:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****              (+++) In CAN IRQ handler, call HAL_CAN_IRQHandler()
  42:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
  43:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       (#) Initialize the CAN peripheral using HAL_CAN_Init() function. This
  44:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           function resorts to HAL_CAN_MspInit() for low-level initialization.
  45:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
  46:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       (#) Configure the reception filters using the following configuration
  47:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           functions:
  48:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****             (++) HAL_CAN_ConfigFilter()
  49:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
  50:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       (#) Start the CAN module using HAL_CAN_Start() function. At this level
  51:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           the node is active on the bus: it receive messages, and can send
  52:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           messages.
  53:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
  54:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       (#) To manage messages transmission, the following Tx control functions
  55:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           can be used:
  56:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****             (++) HAL_CAN_AddTxMessage() to request transmission of a new
  57:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****                  message.
  58:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****             (++) HAL_CAN_AbortTxRequest() to abort transmission of a pending
  59:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****                  message.
  60:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****             (++) HAL_CAN_GetTxMailboxesFreeLevel() to get the number of free Tx
  61:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****                  mailboxes.
  62:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****             (++) HAL_CAN_IsTxMessagePending() to check if a message is pending
  63:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****                  in a Tx mailbox.
  64:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****             (++) HAL_CAN_GetTxTimestamp() to get the timestamp of Tx message
  65:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****                  sent, if time triggered communication mode is enabled.
  66:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
  67:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       (#) When a message is received into the CAN Rx FIFOs, it can be retrieved
  68:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           using the HAL_CAN_GetRxMessage() function. The function
  69:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           HAL_CAN_GetRxFifoFillLevel() allows to know how many Rx message are
  70:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           stored in the Rx Fifo.
  71:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
  72:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       (#) Calling the HAL_CAN_Stop() function stops the CAN module.
  73:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
  74:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       (#) The deinitialization is achieved with HAL_CAN_DeInit() function.
  75:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
  76:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
  77:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       *** Polling mode operation ***
  78:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       ==============================
  79:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     [..]
  80:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       (#) Reception:
  81:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****             (++) Monitor reception of message using HAL_CAN_GetRxFifoFillLevel()
  82:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****                  until at least one message is received.
  83:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****             (++) Then get the message using HAL_CAN_GetRxMessage().
  84:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
  85:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       (#) Transmission:
  86:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****             (++) Monitor the Tx mailboxes availability until at least one Tx
  87:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****                  mailbox is free, using HAL_CAN_GetTxMailboxesFreeLevel().
  88:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****             (++) Then request transmission of a message using
ARM GAS  C:\WINDOWS\ccJNDTLZ.s 			page 3


  89:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****                  HAL_CAN_AddTxMessage().
  90:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
  91:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
  92:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       *** Interrupt mode operation ***
  93:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       ================================
  94:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     [..]
  95:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       (#) Notifications are activated using HAL_CAN_ActivateNotification()
  96:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           function. Then, the process can be controlled through the
  97:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           available user callbacks: HAL_CAN_xxxCallback(), using same APIs
  98:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           HAL_CAN_GetRxMessage() and HAL_CAN_AddTxMessage().
  99:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
 100:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       (#) Notifications can be deactivated using
 101:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           HAL_CAN_DeactivateNotification() function.
 102:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
 103:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       (#) Special care should be taken for CAN_IT_RX_FIFO0_MSG_PENDING and
 104:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           CAN_IT_RX_FIFO1_MSG_PENDING notifications. These notifications trig
 105:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           the callbacks HAL_CAN_RxFIFO0MsgPendingCallback() and
 106:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           HAL_CAN_RxFIFO1MsgPendingCallback(). User has two possible options
 107:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           here.
 108:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****             (++) Directly get the Rx message in the callback, using
 109:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****                  HAL_CAN_GetRxMessage().
 110:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****             (++) Or deactivate the notification in the callback without
 111:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****                  getting the Rx message. The Rx message can then be got later
 112:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****                  using HAL_CAN_GetRxMessage(). Once the Rx message have been
 113:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****                  read, the notification can be activated again.
 114:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
 115:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
 116:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       *** Sleep mode ***
 117:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       ==================
 118:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     [..]
 119:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       (#) The CAN peripheral can be put in sleep mode (low power), using
 120:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           HAL_CAN_RequestSleep(). The sleep mode will be entered as soon as the
 121:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           current CAN activity (transmission or reception of a CAN frame) will
 122:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           be completed.
 123:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
 124:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       (#) A notification can be activated to be informed when the sleep mode
 125:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           will be entered.
 126:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
 127:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       (#) It can be checked if the sleep mode is entered using
 128:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           HAL_CAN_IsSleepActive().
 129:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           Note that the CAN state (accessible from the API HAL_CAN_GetState())
 130:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           is HAL_CAN_STATE_SLEEP_PENDING as soon as the sleep mode request is
 131:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           submitted (the sleep mode is not yet entered), and become
 132:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****           HAL_CAN_STATE_SLEEP_ACTIVE when the sleep mode is effective.
 133:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
 134:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****       (#) The wake-up from sleep mode can be triggered by two ways:
 135:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****             (++) Using HAL_CAN_WakeUp(). When returning from this function,
 136:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****                  the sleep mode is exited (if return status is HAL_OK).
 137:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****             (++) When a start of Rx CAN frame is detected by the CAN peripheral,
 138:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****                  if automatic wake up mode is enabled.
 139:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
 140:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   *** Callback registration ***
 141:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   =============================================
 142:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
 143:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   The compilation define  USE_HAL_CAN_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
 144:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
 145:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   Use Function HAL_CAN_RegisterCallback() to register an interrupt callback.
ARM GAS  C:\WINDOWS\ccJNDTLZ.s 			page 4


 146:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
 147:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   Function HAL_CAN_RegisterCallback() allows to register following callbacks:
 148:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) TxMailbox0CompleteCallback   : Tx Mailbox 0 Complete Callback.
 149:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) TxMailbox1CompleteCallback   : Tx Mailbox 1 Complete Callback.
 150:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) TxMailbox2CompleteCallback   : Tx Mailbox 2 Complete Callback.
 151:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) TxMailbox0AbortCallback      : Tx Mailbox 0 Abort Callback.
 152:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) TxMailbox1AbortCallback      : Tx Mailbox 1 Abort Callback.
 153:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) TxMailbox2AbortCallback      : Tx Mailbox 2 Abort Callback.
 154:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) RxFifo0MsgPendingCallback    : Rx Fifo 0 Message Pending Callback.
 155:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) RxFifo0FullCallback          : Rx Fifo 0 Full Callback.
 156:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) RxFifo1MsgPendingCallback    : Rx Fifo 1 Message Pending Callback.
 157:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) RxFifo1FullCallback          : Rx Fifo 1 Full Callback.
 158:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) SleepCallback                : Sleep Callback.
 159:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) WakeUpFromRxMsgCallback      : Wake Up From Rx Message Callback.
 160:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) ErrorCallback                : Error Callback.
 161:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback              : CAN MspInit.
 162:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback            : CAN MspDeInit.
 163:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
 164:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   and a pointer to the user callback function.
 165:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
 166:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   Use function HAL_CAN_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
 167:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   weak function.
 168:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   HAL_CAN_UnRegisterCallback takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
 169:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   and the Callback ID.
 170:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   This function allows to reset following callbacks:
 171:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) TxMailbox0CompleteCallback   : Tx Mailbox 0 Complete Callback.
 172:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) TxMailbox1CompleteCallback   : Tx Mailbox 1 Complete Callback.
 173:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) TxMailbox2CompleteCallback   : Tx Mailbox 2 Complete Callback.
 174:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) TxMailbox0AbortCallback      : Tx Mailbox 0 Abort Callback.
 175:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) TxMailbox1AbortCallback      : Tx Mailbox 1 Abort Callback.
 176:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) TxMailbox2AbortCallback      : Tx Mailbox 2 Abort Callback.
 177:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) RxFifo0MsgPendingCallback    : Rx Fifo 0 Message Pending Callback.
 178:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) RxFifo0FullCallback          : Rx Fifo 0 Full Callback.
 179:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) RxFifo1MsgPendingCallback    : Rx Fifo 1 Message Pending Callback.
 180:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) RxFifo1FullCallback          : Rx Fifo 1 Full Callback.
 181:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) SleepCallback                : Sleep Callback.
 182:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) WakeUpFromRxMsgCallback      : Wake Up From Rx Message Callback.
 183:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) ErrorCallback                : Error Callback.
 184:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback              : CAN MspInit.
 185:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback            : CAN MspDeInit.
 186:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
 187:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   By default, after the HAL_CAN_Init() and when the state is HAL_CAN_STATE_RESET,
 188:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions:
 189:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   example HAL_CAN_ErrorCallback().
 190:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are
 191:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   reset to the legacy weak function in the HAL_CAN_Init()/ HAL_CAN_DeInit() only when
 192:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 193:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   if not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_CAN_Init()/ HAL_CAN_DeInit()
 194:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand)
 195:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
 196:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_CAN_STATE_READY state only.
 197:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit that can be registered/unregistered
 198:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   in HAL_CAN_STATE_READY or HAL_CAN_STATE_RESET state,
 199:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 200:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 201:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   using HAL_CAN_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_CAN_DeInit()
 202:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   or HAL_CAN_Init() function.
ARM GAS  C:\WINDOWS\ccJNDTLZ.s 			page 5


 203:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c **** 
 204:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   When The compilation define USE_HAL_CAN_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 205:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   not defined, the callback registration feature is not available and all callbacks
 206:./f103/HAL/Src/stm32f1xx_hal_can.c ****   are set to the corresponding weak functions.
